description:
A VerificationSession is the starting-point for a verification flow that will collect and verify data on your users.
Each VerificationSesssion has a URL which provides access to Stripeâ€™s hosted identity verification UI. When you direct your users
to the link, Stripe will collect personal information and verify it. You can retrieve the VerificationSession later to
see the status of the checks performed and access any data collected from your users.

client_secret.description: This string value can be passed to stripe.js to embed a verification flow directly into your app.

created.description: Time at which the object was created. Measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

code.description: A short machine-readable string giving the reason for the verification or user-session failure.

reason.description: A human-readable message giving the reason for the failure. These messages can be shown to your users.

last_error.description: Hash of details on the last error encountered in the verification process.

anyOf.description:
A VerificationReport is the result of an attempt to collect and verify data from a user.
The collection of verification checks performed is determined from the `type` and `options`
parameters used. You can find the result of each verification check performed in the
appropriate sub-resource: `document`, `id_number`, `selfie`.

Each VerificationReport contains a copy of any data collected by the user as well as
reference IDs which can be used to access collected images through the [FileUpload](https://stripe.com/docs/api/files)
API. To configure and create VerificationReports, use the
[VerificationSession](https://stripe.com/docs/api/identity/verification_sessions) API.

Related guides: [Accessing verification results](https://stripe.com/docs/identity/verification-sessions#results).

created.description: Time at which the object was created. Measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.

city.description: City, district, suburb, town, or village.

line1.description: Address line 1 (e.g., street, PO Box, or company name).

line2.description: Address line 2 (e.g., apartment, suite, unit, or building).

address.description: Address as it appears in the document.

dob.description: Date of birth as it appears in the document.

code.description: A short machine-readable string giving the reason for the verification failure.

reason.description: A human-readable message giving the reason for the failure. These messages can be shown to your users.

error.description: Details on the verification error. Present when status is `unverified`.

files.description: Array of [File](https://stripe.com/docs/api/files) ids containing images for this document.

first_name.description: First name as it appears in the document.

last_name.description: Last name as it appears in the document.

code.description: A short machine-readable string giving the reason for the verification failure.

reason.description: A human-readable message giving the reason for the failure. These messages can be shown to your users.

error.description: Details on the verification error. Present when status is `unverified`.

livemode.description: Has the value `true` if the object exists in live mode or the value `false` if the object exists in test mode.

object.description: String representing the object's type. Objects of the same type share the same value.

allowed_types.description: Restrict the list of allowed document type to these types.

require_id_number.description: Require that the user provide an id number which will be verified.

require_live_capture.description: Require that the user capture documents live with their webcam or phone camera.

require_matching_selfie.description: Require that the user provide a selfie to compare against the document photo.

document.description: ID of the [File](https://stripe.com/docs/api/files) holding the image of the identity document used in this check.

code.description: A short machine-readable string giving the reason for the verification failure.

reason.description: A human-readable message giving the reason for the failure. These messages can be shown to your users.

error.description: Details on the verification error. Present when status is `unverified`.

selfie.description: ID of the [File](https://stripe.com/docs/api/files) holding the image of the selfie used in this check.

verification_session.description: ID of the VerificationSession that created this report.

anyOf.title: GelatoVerificationReport

last_verification_report.description: Link to the most recent completed VerificationReport for this Session.
